# Understanding Customer Behaviour and Revenue Drivers in Electronic Sales

1. Project Overview

This project analyses a one-year electronic goods retail dataset (19,999 transactions, September 2023 – September 2024) to answer three research questions about customer purchasing behaviour:

- RQ1 — Do gender and age group differences exist in loyalty conversion, order cancellation, payment method, and shipping preferences?
- RQ2 — Do gender or age group predict price tier preferences within the same product category?
- RQ3 — What factors drive total spending, and does product model price level influence add-on purchasing behaviour?

Core finding:Neither gender nor age is a meaningful segmentation variable. Demographic differences are statistically negligible across all tested indicators. Revenue is driven instead by product type, purchase quantity, and a tiered add-on pricing structure linked to main product price level.


2. Dataset

| Field | Description |
|---|---|
| `Customer ID` | Unique customer identifier |
| `Age` | Customer age (18–80) |
| `Gender` | Male / Female |
| `Loyalty Member` | Yes / No (changes over time) |
| `Product Type` | Smartphone, Laptop, Tablet, Smartwatch, Headphones |
| `SKU` | Product model code (10 distinct SKUs) |
| `Rating` | Product rating 1–5 (no nulls) |
| `Order Status` | Completed / Cancelled |
| `Payment Method` | Credit Card, PayPal, Debit Card, Bank Transfer, Cash |
| `Total Price` | Unit Price × Quantity |
| `Unit Price` | Price per unit (fixed per SKU) |
| `Quantity` | Units purchased (1–10) |
| `Purchase Date` | YYYY-MM-DD |
| `Shipping Type` | Standard, Express, Overnight, Same Day, Expedited |
| `Add-ons Purchased` | Extended Warranty / Accessory / Impulse Item |
| `Add-on Total` | Total add-on spend (billed separately from Total Price) |

Data cleaning notes:
- `Payment Method` had two spellings for PayPal ("PayPal" and "Paypal") — standardised to "PayPal"
- 1 row with missing `Gender` removed → 19,999 rows retained
- 4 single-order anomaly SKUs excluded from RQ2 tier analysis → 19,995 rows


